## T3 Stack Patterns

### tRPC Procedure — Add a New Feature
```ts
// src/server/api/routers/post.ts
import { z } from 'zod';
import { createTRPCRouter, protectedProcedure, publicProcedure } from '@/server/api/trpc';

export const postRouter = createTRPCRouter({
  list: publicProcedure
    .input(z.object({ limit: z.number().default(20) }))
    .query(async ({ ctx, input }) => {
      return ctx.db.post.findMany({
        take: input.limit,
        where: { published: true },
        orderBy: { createdAt: 'desc' },
      });
    }),

  create: protectedProcedure
    .input(z.object({ title: z.string().min(1), content: z.string() }))
    .mutation(async ({ ctx, input }) => {
      return ctx.db.post.create({
        data: { ...input, createdById: ctx.session.user.id },
      });
    }),
});
```

```ts
// src/server/api/root.ts — register new router
import { postRouter } from './routers/post';
export const appRouter = createTRPCRouter({ post: postRouter });
export type AppRouter = typeof appRouter;
```

### Using tRPC in Client Components
```tsx
'use client';
import { api } from '@/trpc/react';

export function PostList() {
  const utils = api.useUtils();

  const { data } = api.post.list.useQuery({ limit: 10 });

  const create = api.post.create.useMutation({
    onSuccess: () => utils.post.list.invalidate(),
  });

  return (
    <>
      <button onClick={() => create.mutate({ title: 'New', content: 'Body' })}>
        Create
      </button>
      {data?.map(p => <p key={p.id}>{p.title}</p>)}
    </>
  );
}
```

### Using tRPC in Server Components
```tsx
// app/page.tsx — Server Component
import { api, HydrateClient } from '@/trpc/server';

export default async function Home() {
  // Prefetch for client component hydration
  void api.post.list.prefetch({ limit: 10 });

  return (
    <HydrateClient>
      <PostList />
    </HydrateClient>
  );
}
```

### Environment Variables (t3-env)
```ts
// src/env.js — all env vars validated here
import { createEnv } from '@t3-oss/env-nextjs';
import { z } from 'zod';

export const env = createEnv({
  server: {
    DATABASE_URL: z.string().url(),
    NEXTAUTH_SECRET: z.string().min(1),
    NEXTAUTH_URL: z.preprocess(
      (str) => process.env.VERCEL_URL ? `https://${process.env.VERCEL_URL}` : str,
      z.string().url()
    ),
  },
  client: {
    NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_URL: z.string().url(),
  },
  runtimeEnv: {
    DATABASE_URL: process.env.DATABASE_URL,
    NEXTAUTH_SECRET: process.env.NEXTAUTH_SECRET,
    NEXTAUTH_URL: process.env.NEXTAUTH_URL,
    NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_URL: process.env.NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_URL,
  },
});
```

### Authentication Check
```ts
// In tRPC procedure (ctx.session is set by protectedProcedure middleware)
// In Server Component:
import { auth } from '@/server/auth';
import { redirect } from 'next/navigation';

export default async function ProtectedPage() {
  const session = await auth();
  if (!session) redirect('/api/auth/signin');
  return <div>Welcome, {session.user.name}</div>;
}
```

### Prisma Schema Pattern
```prisma
// prisma/schema.prisma
model Post {
  id          String   @id @default(cuid())
  title       String
  content     String
  published   Boolean  @default(false)
  createdBy   User     @relation(fields: [createdById], references: [id], onDelete: Cascade)
  createdById String
  createdAt   DateTime @default(now())
  updatedAt   DateTime @updatedAt

  @@index([createdById])
  @@map("posts")
}
```

## Coding Standards

### Type Derivation
- Types come from `z.infer<typeof schema>` or `Prisma.GetPayload<...>` — never handwrite duplicates
- Use `AppRouter` export from `root.ts` as the single type reference for the API
- Use `env.js` for all environment variable access — never `process.env.X` directly

### tRPC Discipline
- `publicProcedure` for read-only, unauthenticated data only
- `protectedProcedure` for anything requiring a user session
- Input schema on every procedure with Zod (even no-input procedures use `z.void()`)

### Data Fetching Rule
- Server Components: use server-side caller (`api.X.query()`)
- Client Components: use `api.X.useQuery()` / `api.X.useMutation()`
- Never mix: don't call `fetch('/api/trpc/...')` directly

## Important Notes

1. **Single API layer** — all data goes through tRPC. No REST endpoints alongside tRPC.
2. **Prisma = source of truth** — schema.prisma defines the data model, not TypeScript interfaces
3. **env.js** — always import `env` from `@/env` to get type-safe, validated env vars
4. **Server/Client boundary** — `src/server/` is NEVER bundled to the client

